cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.RO 

This paper deals with theoretical investigations into off-policy evaluation in reinforcement learning using function approximators for importance weights and value functions. The paper discusses new estimators and provides sample complexity analyses, asymptotic optimality, and insights into the learned importance weights. This work is highly relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), systems and control (cs.SY), and robotics (cs.RO).
